  "text": "Structural and functional comparison of GlpF, seven wAQPs and \"intermediate selectivity channels\" (archeal AQPM and PfAQP from Plasmodium falciparum) suggests a correlation between the pore electrostatic potential profiles and glycerol permeability [CITATION_1] . This strongly suggests that AQP solute specificity cannot be explained by differences in pore size alone.",
